title: Joe’s Amish Chicken Fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350° F. In a plastic bag, mix Panko bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside. In a small bowl, combine garlic and oil. Cut chicken (or have Joe’s staff do this for you!) into 1-inch wide strips. Dip strips in oil; coat with crumb mixture. Place on a non-stick baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

For honey mustard sauce, dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water in a saucepan. Add honey, mustard and remaining water; bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for 1 minute stirring constantly. Serve on side for dipping
